com.github.alexmojaki.caseclasses

Interface FlexiblyEqual

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CaseClass

    public interface FlexiblyEqual
extends CaseClass
    Implementing this class allows greater flexibility for the CaseClasses.equals(CaseClass, Object) method (used by AbstractCaseClass). An instance of a class that implements this interface may be considered equal to another object only if that object is an instance of the class returned by the first instance's equalsBaseClass() method.

      Class equalsBaseClass()
      Return the class that other objects must be an instance of in order to be potentially equal to this object.

    • Method Detail

      • equalsBaseClass

        Class equalsBaseClass()
        Return the class that other objects must be an instance of in order to be potentially equal to this object. The implementation should simply return a constant: either the class that the method is declared in, or an interface that the class implements so that different implementations of the interface can be considered equal.
